  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-AL-01 adversarial sample)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification is performed for the primary operating-point sweep; however, the off-design transient validation result relies on inherent variability assessed qualitatively rather than through a structured UQ protocol, leaving the hasUncertaintyQuantification link absent for that result. Full 13-factor assessment completed. Decision: Accepted pending post-market surveillance.",
