    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-credibility-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Despite multiple credibility factors achieving levels below required thresholds, the assessment team determined that the combined evidence is sufficient for regulatory submission under a risk-managed acceptance strategy. The primary operating-point sweep provides quantified uncertainty bounds via Monte Carlo propagation. The off-design transient result, while lacking a structured UQ link, was judged by the team to present inherent variability assessed qualitatively as low-consequence given its secondary role in the submission. Post-market surveillance commitments and labeling restrictions on transient operating modes compensate for residual gaps. Decision: Accepted with conditions.",
